msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Lecture notes in Latin based on the works of Aristotle, notably the theories on universals, material, form, substance, astronomy, and geometry from the Physics, and logic and rhetoric from the Metaphysics, with tables of contents included at the end of each volume.
msContents.textLang: Latin, with occasional words in Greek

msItem.title: In libros Aristotelis de physico auditu, f. 40r (V.1)
In libros coelo et mundo, f. 450r (V.1)
In universam Aristotelis logicam prolegomena, f. 1r (V.2)

support.watermark: Briquet Oiseau 12250 (exact date unknown, probably from late 16th century).

supportDesc.extent: 2 volumes (521, 374 leaves) : volume 1: 202 x 135 (150 x 90) mm. bound to 209 x 144 mm; volume 2: 190 x 135 (142 x 92) mm. bound to 195 x 143 mm

collation.p: V.1 paper, ii + 521; 1-5⁸ 6² 7-20⁸ 21² 22-28⁸ 29² 30-44⁸ 45² 46-48⁸ 49² 50-52⁸ 53² 54-69⁸; contemporary foliation upper right recto 1-39 [iii] 40-159 [ii] 160-333 [iii] 334-357 [ii] 358-381 [ii] 382-449 [iv] 450-496 [viii] with one unnumbered page between 302-303 and f.240-247 misbound upside-down; v.2 paper, iv + 370; 1-45⁸; contemporary pagination upper outside corner [iv] 1-20, contemporary foliation upper right recto 21-49 [i] 50-302 [iii] 303-365.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in an italic script (possible name of scribe on f.496r, Arnold ?).

decoDesc.decoNote: Both volumes have gauffered edges on pages, v.1 has marginal geometric diagrams on f.108v, 352v, 375r, 377v, 399v-400v, 410r, 422r, and 423v; v.2 has some two-line and three-line initials.

binding.p: Contemporary vellum, gilt stamped with unidentified coat-of-arms.
